    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Yrsa Frostbane leads the Pale Maw Strike Team that attacks Surt’s Forge in Beat 18, but only if Thráinn Ashward was killed in Beat 16. She is battle-worn and grief-hardened, carrying the weight of absolute conviction. She takes command without hesitation and prosecutes the assault with cold efficiency.</p>",
      "director": "<section class=\"secret\"><p><strong>BEAT 18 — Surt’s Forge (conditional: appears only if Thráinn died in Beat 16)</strong></p><p>She/her. Battle-worn, grief-hardened. Visible scars. Carries herself with the weight of someone who has made peace with dying.</p><p><strong>OPENING LINE:</strong> “Thráinn died speaking the truth. I will finish what he started.”</p><p><strong>IN COMBAT:</strong> Same stat block as Pale Maw Strike Leader monster file. Targets Kaelen specifically in rounds 1–2. Positions soldiers to shield her from melee.</p><p><strong>IF DEFEATED:</strong> Her final words, if she has a moment: “You win this moment. Not the argument.”</p><p><strong>TONE:</strong> Unlike Thráinn, she is not intellectually detached — she is grieving. Her certainty is emotional, not philosophical. She is not a fanatic who loves destruction; she is someone who lost something and decided the only correct response was to destroy what killed it. The party may find her more recognizable than Thráinn because of this.</p></section>",
